"A fighter's all I knew how to be, I got the shit beat out of me, tripped and fell and blew out a knee, popped it back in, and hopped up like fuck it, best two-out-of-three." This hit so hard. My parents abused me until my knees started dislocating daily and then neglected my medical care. They hid behind their badge to do it (child abuse prevention officer my ASS). I had to break out of the double-binds, Stockholm syndrome, gaslighting, and paper love to get myself to a surgeon and start surgical repairs that I wouldn't have needed if the abuse had been addressed 12 years sooner.  We all grow up, moms and dads. Be careful what you do while we're still weaker than you.  Our step dad was abusive. We weren't allowed to listen to Eminem, but my mom, brother and I would hide in a car in the parking lot outside the booksamillion in Hampton, Va and listen to his albums when they came out before giving the cd to Kodi (bro) to hide in his walkman. Started in 2000 when I was 8, bro was 11. My mom was a good mom until she became a cop. She wanted protection from her husband, but couldn't leave and support us on babysitting money. Being a cop served both purposes. I guess that made her so comfortable she forgot to look out for us, too. It changed her mental and priorities completely. With her on that fake image 'fear me' bullshit, real dad selling meth, abusive step dad trying to rub my knees/thighs in front of her, and a pedo grandpa enabled by an evil family, I chose Eminem to be my father from afar. Those memories in the parking lot are how I choose to remember my mom. She's still in there somewhere, but so deep that I can't reach her. I circled back 3 times to no avail. It's up to her to save herself now. I will stand by Em's strength and rage at disrespect to his covert moral compass being keystone to my survival. I learned more from Em that I even learned from my own family. I would give my life for Em, but not as a Stan; as a thank you for being my fire when the darkness came collecting souls like a fucking reaper. You will always be the GOAT, Em. ALWAYS.
